changes.new_text:
## 10. Indemnity

10.1 **Each Party shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless the other Party, its Affiliates, and their respective officers, directors, employees and agents** from and against any and all claims, losses, damages, liabilities, costs and expenses (including reasonable legal fees on a full indemnity basis) arising out of or in connection with:

* any breach by the indemnifying Party of this Agreement;

* any negligent act or omission of the indemnifying Party or its personnel;

* any defect in the Goods or Services supplied by the indemnifying Party;

* any infringement or alleged infringement of any third-party Intellectual Property Right arising from the indemnifying Party's supply; and

* any breach by the indemnifying Party of any applicable law or regulation.

[Comment: Mutualised indemnity covering both directions.]{comment: Made mutual (both directions).}

10.2 The indemnities in this clause 10 are ~~uncapped~~ **subject to the limitation of liability in clause 11.1**, save for (i) third-party IP infringement indemnities, which shall remain uncapped, and (ii) indemnities arising from **each Party's** fraud, wilful misconduct, or death or personal injury, which shall remain uncapped.

## 18. Termination

18.1 **Termination for Convenience.** Either Party may terminate this Agreement or any Order at any time **without cause** on **ninety (90) days' written notice** to the other Party. On termination by either Party, Buyer shall reimburse Supplier for: (i) demonstrable direct costs reasonably incurred up to the date of termination, (ii) the reasonable cost of winding down any outstanding Orders, (iii) the cost of-return or disposal of stock held specifically for Buyer's orders, and (iv) a fair proportion of any committed infrastructure or tooling costs amortised over the remaining Term.
[Comment: Made reciprocal with improved compensation.]{comment: Reciprocal 90-day termination with fair compensation for Supplier (demob, stock, tooling).}
